Would you please help me make a test cases for this class? I am working in php and to tests I use PHPUnit 10.
Below I have a class for a user, the instance gets created by supplying a username, email and admin type:

```php
/**
 * Main user class
 */
class User
{
    public $username = null;
    public $email = null;
    public $adminType = null;

    public function __constructor(string $username, string $email, string|AdminType $adminType)
    {
        if(gettype($this->adminType) == "string") {
            switch ($username) {
                case 'a':
                    $this->username = AdminType::SuperAdmin;
                    break;
                case 'b':
                    $this->username = AdminType::Admin;
                    break;
                case 'c':
                    $this->username = AdminType::Moderator;
                    break;
                case 'd':
                    $this->username = AdminType::NormalUser;
                    break;
                default:
                    break;
            }
        } else {
            $this->$adminType = $adminType;
        }
    }
}
```

These are all the admin types:

```php
enum AdminType
{
    case SuperAdmin;
    case Admin;
    case moderator;
    case NormalUser;
}
```

The first test function creates a user instance, then checks if the admin type
is indeed the admin enum.

```php
function testSuperAdminUser()
{
    $newUser = new User('lorem ipsum', 'lorem ipsum', 'a');
    $newUser2 = new User('lorem ipsum', 'lorem ipsum', AdminType::SuperAdmin);
    $this->assertSame($newUser->adminType, AdminType::SuperAdmin);
    $this->assertSame($newUser->adminType, $newUser2->adminType);
}
```

please write test cases for the other Admin types.
Also write tests that assert failure on wrong types. 
Also assert that the adminType in the constructor can be both AdminType emum type or string type.

I have an embedded application written in Rust (so using #![no_std]). I am using the embassy (https://embassy.dev/) as my async runtime. In my program I have two tasks: one data acquisition task, and a data processing task. I want the data gathered in the acquisition task to find its way inside the data processing task. Ideally, I want to only react on new data, as shown in the example below. What are some idiomatic ways to do so?
Here's a rough idea of how my code looks like:
```rust
#[embassy_executor::task]
async fn data_acquisition(mut used_peripherals: UsedPeripherals) {
    let data = sample_data(&mut used_peripherals).await;
    // Now I want to access the data in another task.
}

#[embassy_executor::task]
async fn data_processing() {
    // Somehow wait for new data.
    // Do stuff with the received data.
}
